Keldal:<br>
<br>
Read my post again. I specifically stated in it - I do not condone it. You must have read over that line, or reduced its importance in your mind.<br>
<br>
Personal harassment of any player by any other is unacceptable. I have been on the RECEIVING end of this enough times, purely because of my choice to roleplay. I doubt you are in a position to understand. In a similar way to some man lecturing in a condescending tone a woman who has been raped, on how AWFUL it is to be raped (though obviously not in the same league of seriousness). This does not mean I advocate shooting rapists ( well ... no ... we won't go there ).<br>
<br>
It is not up to anyone to define roleplaying for others to the point of harassment, or harass another for doing it 'their way' (however misguided we may think them).<br>
<br>
To each his own. Always.<br>
<br>
However, I personally will treat those who spam public channels (especially auction) with OOC nonsense with disdain, and I encourage others to do so as well, in the hope of stamping it out. Sorry if you disagree, but we all get to try to mold the community the way we want it. I will similarly be far more sympathetic than average to any who approach me in a roleplay-style, and considerably less so to any who address me with d00d speak. So the extremist non-roleplayer might call me some RP extremist, though actually I am not, I think every person should be able to play they want to and makes them happy, and I have many non-roleplaying friends who just are happy doing what they do, and I group with them lots. But I still question the motives of anyone who actually HATES roleplaying, or even just professes a total indifference towards roleplaying, coming to play the the server tagged as RP (with whatever riders you like). ALL the other servers are not so tagged. Yes, it's a free world, players can play where they want, but coming to the RP server and spamming public channels with d00d speak is like throwing petrol on a fire; it is not exactly keeping it to yourself, it is trying to negatively impact the RP experience of everyone else in the zone.<br>
<br>
My previous post was an explanation of where I believe some harsher feelings are coming from, not an excuse for the behaviour. Understanding a problem is the key to solving it. Blind soapbox statements solve nothing (except to antagonise the readers into thinking you condescending). There will be a bit of a backlash for a time. But this will, I truly believe, become less prominent, as people settle down to enjoying their new environment, and spread out across the zones of Norrath.<br>
<br>
/bow <p>------------------------------------------------<BR><BR>
